Jill and the author send warm wishes to the Orthodox Christian community for Easter. They celebrate the Resurrection of Jesus Christ and the victory of light over darkness. They also pray for those suffering from war and persecution, and express sympathy for those who have lost loved ones or fear for their safety. They pledge to work for peace, justice, freedom, and security for all people. They acknowledge the contributions of Orthodox Christians through compassion, interfaith solidarity, advocacy for religious freedom, and care for the environment. They encourage spreading the message of Easter joy by building a world that respects the dignity and worth of every person. They conclude by wishing peace and a happy Easter to all.